
[1]flexure

   FLEX'URE, n. [L. flexura.]

   1. A winding or bending; the form of bending; as the flexure of a
   joint.

   2. The act of bending.

   3. The part bent; a joint.

   4. The bending of the body; obsequious or servile cringe.
